get_timepoints <- function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    12x
                    
                      
    assert_that(length(x) == length(unique(x)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    12x
                    
                      
    x_ord <- x[order(x)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    12x
                    
                      
    x_no_neg <- x_ord[x_ord >= 0]

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    12x
                    
                      
    bound_lower <- c(0, x_no_neg[-length(x_no_neg)])

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    12x
                    
                      
    bound_upper <- x_no_neg

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    12x
                    
                      
    bound_width <- bound_upper - bound_lower

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    12x
                    
                      
    eval_points <- bound_upper - bound_width / 2

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    12x
                    
                      
    tibble::tibble(

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    12x
                    
                      
        lower = bound_lower,

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    12x
                    
                      
        upper = bound_upper,

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    12x
                    
                      
        eval = eval_points,

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    12x
                    
                      
        time = bound_upper,

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    12x
                    
                      
        width = bound_width

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
}

                    10
                    2x
                    
                      
    function(time) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    2x

#' Construct a Log Hazard Function for the Log-Logistic Model

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lambda (`number`)\cr the inverse median parameter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' @param p (`number`)\cr the shape parameter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A function of `time` returning the log hazard.

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
sim_os_loglogistic <- function(lambda, p) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    function(time) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
        c1 <- log(lambda) + log(p) + (p - 1) * (log(lambda) + log(time))

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
        c2 <- log(1 + (lambda * time)^p)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
        return(c1 - c2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    40

                    21

                    22

#' @returns The `data` after removing observations that contain missing values in the required variables.

remove_missing_rows <- function(data, formula, extra_vars) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    26x
                    
                      
    extra_vars <- paste(extra_vars, collapse = " + ")

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    26x
                    
                      
    formula_update_string <- paste0(". ~ . + ", extra_vars)

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    26x
                    
                      
    formula_update <- stats::update(formula, formula_update_string)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    26x
                    
                      
    missing_rows <- get_missing_rownumbers(data, formula_update)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    26x
                    
                      
    if (length(missing_rows) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    23x
                    
                      
        return(data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    3x
                    
                      
    message(sprintf(

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    3x
                    
                      
        "Note that %d observations were removed as one of more required variables contained missing values",

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    3x
                    
                      
        length(missing_rows)

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    3x
                    
                      
    data[-missing_rows, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Obtain Median and Credible Intervals from MCMC samples

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
#' @param samples (`matrix`)\cr with samples in rows and parameters in columns.

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
#' @param level (`number`)\cr credibility level to use for the credible intervals.

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A `data.frame` with columns `median`, `lower` and `upper`.

#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
#' set.seed(123)

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
#' samples <- cbind(rnorm(100, 0, 1), rexp(100, 0.5), rpois(100, 5))

#' samples_median_ci(samples)

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
samples_median_ci <- function(samples, level = 0.95) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    556x
                    
                      
    assert_that(is.matrix(samples))

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    556x
                    
                      
    assert_that(is.number(level), level < 1, level > 0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    556x
                    
                      
    samples_median <- apply(samples, MARGIN = 2L, FUN = stats::median)

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    556x
                    
                      
    probs <- c((1 - level) / 2, (1 + level) / 2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    556x
                    
                      
    samples_ci <- t(apply(samples, MARGIN = 2L, FUN = stats::quantile, probs = probs))

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    556x
                    
                      
    colnames(samples_ci) <- c("lower", "upper")

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    556x
                    
                      
    as.data.frame(cbind(

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    556x
                    
                      
        median = samples_median,

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    556x
                    
                      
        samples_ci

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
}

                    48x

                    193x

        if (is.null(results[[block]])) {

    function(object) { #nolint

## sim_lm_gsf ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' Generalized Stein-Fojo Functionals

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param time (`numeric`)\cr time grid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param b (`number`)\cr baseline.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param s (`number`)\cr shrinkage.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param g (`number`)\cr growth.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param phi (`number`)\cr shrinkage proportion.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns The function results.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' gsf_sld(1:10, 20, 0.3, 0.6, 0.2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
gsf_sld <- function(time, b, s, g, phi) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    7x
                    
                      
    b * (phi * exp(-s * time) + (1 - phi) * exp(g * time))

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @rdname gsf_sld

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' gsf_ttg(1:10, 20, 0.3, 0.6, 0.2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
gsf_ttg <- function(time, b, s, g, phi) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    2x
                    
                      
    t1 <- (log(s * phi / (g * (1 - phi))) / (g + s))

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    2x
                    
                      
    t1[t1 <= 0] <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    2x
                    
                      
    return(t1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' @rdname gsf_sld

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' gsf_dsld(1:10, 20, 0.3, 0.6, 0.2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
gsf_dsld <- function(time, b, s, g, phi) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    2x
                    
                      
    t1 <- (1 - phi) * g * exp(g * time)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    2x
                    
                      
    t2 <- phi * s * exp(-s * time)

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    2x
                    
                      
    return(b * (t1 - t2))

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#' Construct a Simulation Function for Longitudinal Data from GSF Model

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#' @param sigma (`number`)\cr the variance of the longitudinal values.

#' @param mu_s (`numeric`)\cr the mean shrinkage rates for the two treatment arms.

                    		
                  

                  

                    51

#' @param omega_phi (`number`)\cr the shrinkage proportion standard deviation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#' @param link_dsld (`number`)\cr the link coefficient for the derivative contribution.

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#' @param link_ttg (`number`)\cr the link coefficient for the time-to-growth contribution.

#' @param link_identity (`number`)\cr the link coefficient for the SLD Identity contribution.

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A function with argument `lm_base` that can be used to simulate

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
#'   longitudinal data from the corresponding GSF model.

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
sim_lm_gsf <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
    sigma = 0.01,

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
    mu_s = c(3, 4),

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
    mu_g = c(0.2, 0.3),

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
    mu_phi = c(0.1, 0.2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
    mu_b = 50,

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
    omega_b = 0.135,

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
    omega_s = 0.15,

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
    omega_g = 0.225,

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
    omega_phi = 0.75,

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
    link_dsld = 0,

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
    link_ttg = 0,

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    link_identity = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    2x
                    
                      
    function(lm_base) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    2x
                    
                      
        assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(unique(lm_base$study)) == 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(mu_b) == 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(sigma) == 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(mu_s) == length(unique(lm_base$arm)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(mu_s) == length(mu_g),

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(mu_s) == length(mu_phi),

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    2x
                    
                      
            length(c(omega_b, omega_s, omega_g, omega_phi)) == 4

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    2x
                    
                      
        baseline_covs <- lm_base |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::distinct(.data$pt, .data$arm, .data$study) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(arm_n = as.numeric(factor(as.character(.data$arm)))) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(eta_b = stats::rnorm(dplyr::n(), 0, 1)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(eta_s = stats::rnorm(dplyr::n(), 0, 1)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(eta_g = stats::rnorm(dplyr::n(), 0, 1)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(eta_phi = stats::rnorm(dplyr::n(), 0, 1)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(psi_b = exp(log(mu_b) + .data$eta_b * omega_b)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(psi_s = exp(log(mu_s[.data$arm_n]) + .data$eta_s * omega_s)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    2x
                    
                      
            dplyr::mutate(psi_g = exp(log(mu_g[.data$arm_n]) + .data$eta_g * omega_g)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    2x

                    33

                    34

                    6x

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
        stop("`random_slope` must be a `prior_none()`")

                    		
                  

                  

                    44

                    46
                    6x

                    49

                    51
                    6x

                    52
                    6x
                    
                      
                Parameter(name = "lm_rs_slope_sigma", prior = slope_sigma, size = 1),
